<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-receipts-heading">
  <h1 class="api-page-title" id="api-receipts-heading">What a receipt means</h1>
  <ul class="api-list">
    <li>
      Every response names its contract in a <code>schema</code> tag, and every fact lands in an
      append-only journal beside content-addressed artifacts. Read endpoints re-verify stored
      receipts instead of trusting storage; the caption read re-hashes the full authority chain,
      and tamper fails the whole read.
    </li>
    <li>
      Unavailable, unknown, withheld, truncated, and failed are first-class states that survive
      every projection. The API returns an honest empty list before a fluent guess.
    </li>
    <li>
      Passing an audit proves integrity and citation closure, not semantic truth or translation
      quality. Semantic claims live on the <a href="/benchmarks/">benchmarks page</a> with their
      own receipts.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
